subject: Artifacts deployed to maven 2 central repository

messageBody:
I had some trouble resolving the latest version of JUnit from the
central repository. Brief investigation revealed that it is due to the
metadata not being properly updated to include the new versions [1],
although 4.3 and 4.3.1 are hosted there. This causes problems when
using maven ranges, as 4.2 is determined to be the newest. Does the
JUnit community handle deployment, or should I look elsewhere?

Thanks,
Stephen Pack

[1] http://repo1.maven.org/maven2/junit/junit/maven-metadata.xml
